author: CNN
description: US President Donald Trump wrote on social media that he has ordered the Defense Department to prepare for possible military action in Nigeria as he continues to accuse the nation of not doing enough to stem violence against Christians — an accusation Nigeria has repeatedly denied. CNN's Larry Madowo explains what is actually happening on the ground. #cnn #news #nigeria
title: Trump threatens to send US troops to Nigeria

author: CNN
description: CNN's Fareed Zakaria speaks with Qatari Prime Minister Sheikh Mohammed bin Abdulrahman Al-Thani for his first TV interview since the Israel-Hamas ceasefire. They discuss the recent truce violations in Gaza – and what kind of peacekeeping force should eventually govern the strip. #CNN #News
title: Qatari Prime Minister on Israel’s ‘disproportionate’ attack on Gaza during the ceasefire

author: CNN
description:
Sen. John Fetterman said today that his Democratic colleagues need to own their role in the federal government shutdown as Americans begin to lose food assistance benefits and more federal workers miss paychecks. The Pennsylvania Democrat called it “deeply distressing” that SNAP benefits ran dry for many people this weekend, telling CNN’s Jake Tapper on “State of the Union” that he refuses “to put 42 million Americans in the kinds of food insecurity.” Fetterman is one of three members of the Senate Democratic caucus who has voted repeatedly with Republicans in support of a stopgap bill to fund the government through November 21.

Jake Tapper discusses the upcoming election with his "State of the Union" panel: Rep. Buddy Carter (R-GA), CNN political commentator Ashley Allison, Republican strategist Kristin Davison, and CNN political commentator and former New York City mayor Bill de Blasio.  #CNN #News
title: One-on-one with Sen. John Fetterman (D-PA)

author: CNN
description: Jake Tapper pushes House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries (D-NY) on if Democrats should reopen the government in the wake of SNAP benefits expiring and whether Zohran Mamdani will be the future of the Democratic Party if he wins the New York City mayoral race this week. #CNN #News
title: One-on-one with House Democratic Leader Hakeem Jeffries

author: CNN
description:
Clocks have just "fallen back" one hour, marking the end of daylight saving time as most states in the US return to standard time. But why does most of the country follow this practice, and where did it begin? CNN's Jake Tapper explains the history of daylight saving time and why it’s likely to continue for most Americans for years to come.

#CNN #News #daylightsavingtime
title: Why we can’t get rid of daylight saving time

#cnn #news #worldseries #basketball #dodgers #bluejays

author: CNN
description:
Nine people were left with life-threatening injuries from a stabbing attack on a passenger train in Cambridgeshire, England, on Saturday, police said. Two British nationals have been arrested, and there is no indication the attack was terror-related, according to British Transport Police. CNN's Nic Robertson reports.

#CNN #News #England
title: Two arrested in stabbing attack on UK train

author: CNN
description:
UK police have ruled out terrorism in relation to Saturday’s mass stabbing attack on a train in central England, as two people remain in a life-threatening condition in hospital. Two British-born men were arrested in connection to the attack, that saw 10 people taken to the hospital by ambulance while another person later self-presented that evening. As of Sunday morning, two victims remain in a life-threatening condition, British Transport Police Superintendent John Loveless told reporters.

CNN international diplomatic editor Nic Robertson reports, and CNN's Kim Brunhuber speaks with former Metropolitan Police chief superintendent Dal Babu. #CNN #News
title: UK police: 'Nothing to suggest' train stabbings were 'a terrorist incident'
